HEADWORD: Frogmouth
<hw>Frog"mouth`</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <fld>(Zool.)</fld>
<def>One of several species of Asiatic and East Indian birds of the
genus <gen>Batrachostomus</gen> (family <fam>Podargid⟦ae⟧</fam>); -- so
called from their very broad, flat bills.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

